article.description: Marvelle Harris scored 18 points to move into fourth place on the Fresno State list of all-time top scorers and the Bulldogs rolled past Nevada, 95-63, in a Mountain West Conference contest Wedne
article.headline: Harris' 18 points leads Fresno State past Nevada, 85-63
article.linkText: Harris' 18 points leads Fresno State past Nevada, 85-63
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- Marvelle Harris scored 18 points to move into fourth place on the Fresno State list of all-time top scorers and the Bulldogs rolled past Nevada, 95-63, in a Mountain West Conference contest Wednesday night. Fresno State (10-5, 1-1) rebounded from what it considered a very poor showing in a loss to New Mexico in its last game, falling behind early and trailing by as many as 24 points in the second half. Harris came into the game two points shy of tying Carl Ray Harris. He shot 7 of 15 from the floor, grabbed seven rebounds and passed out seven assists. Karachi Edo contributed 15 points. Marqueze Coleman scored 22 points and Cameron Oliver added 13 for Nevada (9-5, 1-1), which entered the game averaging a conference-best 79.6 points per game, but was just 18 of 51 from the field and 1 of 13 from long range.
